description:
What lessons from nature can we learn that reveal God's character and plan for His creation? Co-dependence explains the harmony and interdependence existing in the natural world. Walter Veith looks at examples in nature that give us glimpses of what the world must have been like before sin. 
How do beauty in nature, the specificity of certain pollinators, and the soil food web defy evolution? What do the earth’s resource cycles – the energy, water, oxygen, carbon, and nitrogen cycles – teach about God’s plan for His people?

Unselfishness is the underlying principle of Creation and must become the principle of our lives and character. How can we apply this principle in the work of the church?
